title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 20 § 266.2 - City of Yonkers taxable wages and net earnings from self-employment applicable to nonresident period
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 20 § 266.2 - City of Yonkers taxable wages and net earnings from self-employment applicable to nonresident period

State Regulations

Tax Law, § 12(b) of § 1340(c); Codes and Ordinances of the

City of Yonkers, § 92-109(b)

The City of Yonkers taxable wages and net earnings from
self-employment of a taxpayer applicable to the portion of the year during
which such taxpayer is a nonresident of the City of Yonkers must be determined, except as provided in section
266.3
of this Part, as if such taxpayer's taxable year for Federal income tax
purposes were limited to the period of nonresident status. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 20
§
266.2

comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
